description: A Soviet space platform known as Tri-Vee which is also an archival and reconstruction super-visory unit, has circled the world for 40 years. Last of the old world and herald of the new, Tri-Vee takes control of the new humans spacecraft and sets them on a new course.
name: Relics

description: The Shattered Earth Chronicles
name: Masquerade

description: Who is Infantry? What is his agenda? Is he a new hero of the people... or merely a pawn in a larger game? The hordes of NEMESIS are America's greatest enemy, attacking it from within at its highest levels of power. What does this have to do with a mysterious super-agent, the lone survivor of a doomed experiment in human peformance enhancement?

Insurance investigator Charlie Alexander has stumbled upon a mystery that could have global implications. While the masked soldier known as Infantry makes himself the number one enemy of NEMESIS, Charlie slowly tears at the shroud of secrecy surrounding the destruction of a aboratory hidden in the south pacific - an investigation that makes him a target of NEMESIS, the C.I.A., and possibly Infantry himself...
name: "Leg Breaker Confidential"

description: Charlie Alexander is just a normal, workaday insurance investigator who has stumbled onto an incredible mystery. After coming face to face with the man called Infantry, Charlie is more determined than ever to find out who he is. But what possible answers could be held by an elderly man in a remote part of Wyoming? And while Charlie edges ever closer to understanding, Infantry himself is hunted by the unstable "Slither." A political thriller wrapped up in an action tale.

Even as Charlie Alexander begins to uncover some truths behind his recent encounters with the C.I.A. and its connection to his investigation, the mystery surrounding the man called Infantry deepens. How is he connected to a century-old man who claims to have once been the country’s greatest weapon? While Charlie digs for the facts, Infantry confronts the three most deadly assassins in the world!

Jimmy the Turtle Food Collector

Jimmy the Silly Retard collects food for turtles. Luckily his old pal George Liquor is willing to help him out.
name: In Service to Mankind

description:
A thrilling collection of some of the greatest races between the Man of Steel and the Scarlet Speedster, from SUPERMAN #199, THE FLASH #175, WORLD'S FINEST COMICS #198, WORLD'S FINEST COMICS #199, DC COMICS PRESENTS #1-2, and more!

Back Blurb

Over the years, people have wondered who was faster, the Man of Steel or the Scarlet Speedster. Various teams of writers and artists have explored that question and for the first time ever, all the classic contests have been collected.

See them race on land, on sea, in space and through time - with unexpected challenges, dangers and surprises along each course.
name: TPB

description: In the past, Superman has had no trouble handling Maxima, Barrage, Riot, Anomaly, and Misa in individual battle. But when a criminal mastermind unites these deadly villains, the Man of Steel finds himself in serious trouble. United by their singular objective of the death of Superman, these super powered rogues wreak havoc on Metropolis and the last son of Krypton. However, having trouble working together, the Revenge Squad starts fighting within their own ranks, granting Superman gets his one and only opportunity for survival and victory.
name: TPB

description: DC presents several of the best comics stories featuring Superman battling his arch-nemesis! Witness the various incarnations of Luthor in stories from ACTION COMICS #23, 544, ADVENTURE COMICS #271, SUPERBOY #86, #139, SUPERMAN (vol. 1) #90, #164, #416, MAN OF STEEL #4, SUPERMAN (vol. 2) #9, #131 and SUPERMAN: LEX 2000!
name: TPB

description:
Who are The Socials, and what is their mysterious agenda in moving young people across the city in self-organizing crowds? Is it mind-control – or simply boredom? What starts as fun and games becomes deadly serious and leads to an unexpected confrontation between

Red Robin and Robin in this new collection from issues #13-17.
name: TPB

description:
Juanita Jean Sachs is a model-turned-crusader. Ernie "Violens" Schultz is a war-scarred photographer with major anger management issues. Cross them at your own risk.

They are two people who battle some of the greatest evils of our society: Pornography. Murder. White Slavery. Religious fanaticism. And why do they do it? Because they get an erotic charge from risking their lives.

SACHS AND VIOLENS created a sensation when their miniseries first debuted in 1993. Now, for the first-time ever, the saga from New York Times best-selling author Peter David (AQUAMAN, Star Trek: Imzadi) and acclaimed artist George Pérez (CRISIS ON INFINITE EARTHS, JLA/AVENGERS) is collected in a single volume, with a new cover by Pérez and an introduction from David!
name: TPB

This first of three volumes collecting Lee's one-of-a-kind one-shots reprints JUST IMAGINE STAN LEE WITH JOE KUBERT CREATING BATMAN, ...WITH JIM LEE CREATING WONDER WOMAN, ...WITH JOHN BUSCEMA CREATING SUPERMAN, and ...WITH DAVE GIBBONS CREATING GREEN LANTERN!
name: Book 1

volume.name: Just Imagine Stan Lee Creating the DC Universe

description: A second collection of Stan Lee's revolutionary re-imaginings of the DC Universe's mightiest icons! This volume reprints JUST IMAGINE STAN LEE WITH KEVIN MAGUIRE CREATING THE FLASH, ...WITH JERRY ORDWAY CREATING THE JLA , ...WITH JOHN BYRNE CREATING ROBIN, ...WITH GARY FRANK CREATING SHAZAM, and more!
name: Book 2

volume.name: Just Imagine Stan Lee Creating the DC Universe

description: Collecting the final four issues of Stan Lee's celebrated re-interpretation of the DC Universe! Don't miss Lee teaming with Scott McDaniel on Aquaman, Walter Simonson on Sandman and Chris Bachalo on Catwoman, then wrapping it all up with a brand new Crisis, drawn by John Cassaday! Plus, all four artists share remembrances and sketch material, movie producer Michael Uslan (BATMAN: DETECTIVE No. 27) provides an introduction, Stan Lee contributes an afterword, and Adam Hughes turns in a stunning new cover image!
name: Book 3

volume.name: Just Imagine Stan Lee Creating the DC Universe

description: From 1914 to 1918, Hans Von Hammer earned the nickname "The Hammer of Hell" in the bloody skies of World War I. Now it's World War II, and blood rains from the skies once again! Von Hammer, the finest pilot Germany has ever known, is now a 46-year-old man with plenty of enemies in the Nazi regime. This edition also includes a classic World War One Enemy Ace tale by creators Robert Kanigher and Joe Kubert reprinted from STAR-SPANGLED WAR STORIES #139!
name: TPB
